Text:
Today I'm feeling great and really looking forward to my eye test.

 The reason I have come for a sight test today is because I've noticed my distance vision is no longer as good as it was, and I don't have any glasses for my distance vision. My distance vision has been getting worse slowly over about 6 months. Because my distance vision is not so good I'm less confident about driving than I used to be. My distance vision is a little blurred all the time, it does not change.

Because my distance vision is not so good I'm less confident about driving than I used to be. My distance vision is a little blurred all the time, it does not change.

 I do however wear glasses for reading. I've been wearing reading glasses for the past 15 years and I can see well with them. My current reading glasses are about 4 years old I think.

I've been wearing reading glasses for the past 15 years and I can see well with them. My current reading glasses are about 4 years old I think. I'm not really having any other visual problems but I do get headaches occasionally.

 I don't wear contact lenses.

 My last eye test was about 4 years ago I think, I'm not too sure.

I don't wear contact lenses.

 My last eye test was about 4 years ago I think, I'm not too sure.

 Over the last year I've been getting dull headaches, on and off, on the side of my head, around once a week, when doing computer work or reading for long periods of time. Luckily, I don't get any eyestrain but the headaches are getting annoying. If my headaches get really bad I take a paracetamol tablet occasionally.

Luckily, I don't get any eyestrain but the headaches are getting annoying. If my headaches get really bad I take a paracetamol tablet occasionally.

 I don't get any double vision or floaters.   For several years I've been getting flashes in my vision every night, not sure if its happening in both eyes or just one. Usually I just notice the flashing lights when I get up to go to the loo and the house is dark, its no big deal.

For several years I've been getting flashes in my vision every night, not sure if its happening in both eyes or just one. Usually I just notice the flashing lights when I get up to go to the loo and the house is dark, its no big deal. Other than the flashing lights at night, I haven't noticed anything else odd about my vision. I don't get any floating things in my vision. I don't experience any pain or itching with my eyes but sometimes they feel dry and they are a bit red.

I don't get any floating things in my vision. I don't experience any pain or itching with my eyes but sometimes they feel dry and they are a bit red. My eyes were not patched when I was a child. 

 30 years ago I was discharged from the hospital after having cyst removal surgery and being prescribed lid scrubs for my blepharitis, that was the only time I went to the eye hospital. It was an eye opening experience.

30 years ago I was discharged from the hospital after having cyst removal surgery and being prescribed lid scrubs for my blepharitis, that was the only time I went to the eye hospital. It was an eye opening experience. 

 My family don't have any eye or health problems. No one in my family has health problems such as diabetes or high blood pressure. My dad did have cataracts when he was about 70 years old.

No one in my family has health problems such as diabetes or high blood pressure. My dad did have cataracts when he was about 70 years old. 

 My general health is good. I don't have diabetes but I am genetically predisposed to type 2 diabetes, and my last medical exam was 2 months ago to get my blood sugar levels checked. I take vitamin D and cod liver oil supplements.

I don't have diabetes but I am genetically predisposed to type 2 diabetes, and my last medical exam was 2 months ago to get my blood sugar levels checked. I take vitamin D and cod liver oil supplements. I do not take any medication, pills or tablets. Around May time I may take antihistamines and sometimes steroid drops if my hay fever really flares up. I don't smoke since I know it's damaging to my health.

 I work (occupation; do for a living) as a teacher. I work in a local secondary school as teacher. It's rewarding working as a teacher but it can be hard work too.

I work in a local secondary school as teacher. It's rewarding working as a teacher but it can be hard work too. I am a teacher at a local secondary school (work, occupation, do for a living).

 I spend about 6 hours a day looking at my computer screen. It's too long really

I spend about 6 hours a day looking at my computer screen. It's too long really and I wonder if that is contributing to my headaches.

 I drive to work most days in the car but occasionally I go on my motorbike. Its more fun going by motorbike but no so great when it is raining.

I drive to work most days in the car but occasionally I go on my motorbike. Its more fun going by motorbike but no so great when it is raining. My motorbike is a KTM SMT 990, its a bit of a handful and makes me feel like a bit of a hooligan sometimes. 

 My main hobbies are motorcycling and climbing on the weekends. Mostly I climb at the local climbing wall but sometimes, I go to the Alps on a big climbing trip as a holiday.
